Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[When the (continuously updated) DVFA map addressing COVID-19 in minks was accessed yesterday (13 Oct 2020) afternoon, the total number of infected mink holdings in Denmark was 76; their number, 24 hours later (Wed 14 Oct 2020 afternoon), is 89. The virus is circulating in mink farms in 8 municipalities, distributed in 2 of Denmark's 5 main regions, namely, in North Jutland (in 6 municipalities out of 11) and in Mid Jutland (in 2 municipalities out of 19). This is a sharp daily increase that deserves clarification. The map and the said data are available at https://www.foedevarestyrelsen.dk/Leksikon/Sider/Kort-over-screening-af-COVID-19-i-mink.aspx.

The last (4th) OIE update from Denmark on its COVID-19 situation in farmed minks was submitted 1 Oct 2020 (available at https://www.oie.int/fileadmin/Home/MM/Update_4_Letter_to_OIE_on_Sars-CoV-2_in_mink_farms_in_Denmark.pdf). It informed that "in order to mitigate the current situation, additional activities have been initiated, including intensified frequency of sampling (twice a week) of all dead mink in a herd in the relevant municipalities." Such enhanced sampling frequency could have partially contributed to the increased number of reported infected holdings. However, since the number of infected municipalities was, at that point in time, reported to be 2 (Hjorring and Fredeikshavn), there should be other factors behind the spatial spread of the disease in the Danish mink farms located in 8 municipalities. Updated official information on the epidemiology of the disease, the revised control policy, its background and estimated culling figures will be helpful. - Mod.AS

